Explain the difference between Statement and Prepared Statements.

Answer:--

Statement:---
Statement is a Interface used to execute string based SQL queries.
it accepts strings as Sql queries. by the use of this the code become less readable.

Syntax:-
Statement s=conn.createStatement();

PreparedStatement:---
PreparedStatement is a interface used to execute parameterized SQL queries.
it has methods to bind various objects.by the use of this the code becomes more understandable.

sysntax:--

PreparedStatement ps=conn.prepareStatement("sql query");
